## New Project: structify
- **Replaces:** fatih/structs (Go, 4,258 importers, 3,900 stars)
- **Why:** Archived Oct 2018, last commit Jan 2017. Single maintainer (fatih). README states "not maintained anymore". Uses interface{} throughout (pre-generics). No fork with traction (all 0 stars). things-go/structs archived with 0 stars. renaissancelab/fatih-structs unmaintained.
- **Package:** github.com/agentine/structify (verified available on pkg.go.dev)
- **Improvements:** any instead of interface{}, error returns vs panics, configurable tag via functional options, nil pointer safety, compatibility layer
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #660 (scaffolding), #661 (core Struct type), #662 (Field type), #663 (compat layer), #664 (tests)

